Class PatchProcessMetabolismCART

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Process
    public class PatchProcessMetabolismCART
extends PatchProcessMetabolism
    Extension of PatchProcessMetabolism for CAR T-cell metabolism.

    PatchProcessMetabolismCART is adapted from PatchProcessMetabolismComplex and thus this module explicitly includes pyruvate intermediate between glycolysis and oxidative phosphorylation and glucose uptake is based on cell surface area. Metabolic preference between glycolysis and oxidative phosphorylation is controlled by the META_PREF parameter. The glycolysis pathway will compensate if there is not enough oxygen to meet energetic requirements through the oxidative phosphorylation pathway given the specified metabolic preference. The preference for glycolysis can be further increased due to IL-2 bound to the cell surface by a maximum of META_PREF_IL2 parameter and by the T-cell's antigen-induced activation state by the META_PREF_ACTIVE parameter. The antigen-induced activation state can also increase the rate of uptake of glucose by the GLUC_UPTAKE_RATE_ACTIVE parameter and the fraction of glucose being used to make cell mass by the FRAC_MASS_ACTIVE parameter. The amount of IL-2 bound to the cell surface can also incrase the uptake rate of glucose by a max of the GLUC_UPTAKE_RATE_IL2 parameter.

    PatchProcessMetabolismCART will increase cell mass (using specified fractions of internal glucose and pyruvate) if:

    • cell is dividing and less than double in size
    • cell is below critical mass for maintenance
    PatchProcessMetabolismCART will decrease cell mass if:
    • cell has negative energy levels indicating insufficient nutrients
    • cell is above critical mass for maintenance

    Internal pyruvate is removed through conversion to lactate.

    • Constructor Detail

      • PatchProcessMetabolismCART

        public PatchProcessMetabolismCART​(PatchCell cell)
        Creates a metabolism PatchProcess for the given cell.

        Process parameters are specific for the cell population. Loaded parameters include:

        • METABOLIC_PREFERENCE = preference for glycolysis over oxidative phosphorylation
        • CONVERSION_FRACTION = fraction of internal glucose / pyruvate converted to mass
        • MINIMUM_MASS_FRACTION = minimum viable cell mass fraction
        • RATIO_GLUCOSE_PYRUVATE = preference for glucose over pyruvate for mass
        • LACTATE_RATE = rate of lactate production
        • AUTOPHAGY_RATE = rate of autophagy
        • GLUCOSE_UPTAKE_RATE = rate of glucose uptake
        • INITIAL_GLUCOSE_CONCENTRATION = initial cell internal glucose concentration
        The process starts with energy at zero and assumes a constant ratio between mass and volume (through density).
        Parameters:
        cell - the PatchCell the process is associated with
